'''Femerell''', originally '''fumerell''' (from O. Fr. ''fumeraille'', Lat, ''fumus'', smoke), is the [[old English]] term given to the [[lantern]], [[louvre]], or covering placed in the ridge of a hall [[roof]] for the purpose of ventilation or letting out the [[smoke]] of the fire kindled on a central hearth.

